WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.476 --> 00:00:08.178
<i>Previously on</i>
Criminal Minds: Evolution...

2
00:00:08.278 --> 00:00:11.047
They will let anybody up
on the sixth floor now. huh?

3
00:00:11.147 --> 00:00:13.984
<i>Alvez and I</i>
are retired Army grunts.

4
00:00:14.117 --> 00:00:15.519
We met in the ARC Program.

5
00:00:15.652 --> 00:00:17.354
The Army Recovery Care Program.

6
00:00:17.488 --> 00:00:19.856
We help ill and injured
service members

7
00:00:19.990 --> 00:00:22.158
reintegrate into civilian life.

8
00:00:22.258 --> 00:00:23.694
<i>The tumor's spread.</i>

9
00:00:23.794 --> 00:00:25.396
<i>There's nothing else we can do.</i>

10
00:00:27.030 --> 00:00:28.664
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

11
00:00:28.665 --> 00:00:31.535
Hey. Sorry to interrupt.
Do you have a second?

12
00:00:31.635 --> 00:00:33.003
If you'll excuse me.

13
00:00:33.103 --> 00:00:34.671
<i>Did you notice
how he checked you out?</i>

14
00:00:34.805 --> 00:00:36.940
<i>You look like his wife
who just left him.</i>

15
00:00:37.040 --> 00:00:39.209
Welcome to <i>The Sicarius Files.</i>

16
00:00:39.342 --> 00:00:41.176
I'm your host. Brian Garrity.

17
00:00:41.177 --> 00:00:43.279
My guest.
the Sicarius Killer himself.

18
00:00:43.380 --> 00:00:45.348
Elias Voit.

19
00:00:46.517 --> 00:00:48.084
Whoa!

20
00:00:50.253 --> 00:00:52.022
Saved you a whole bunch
of fan letters.

21
00:00:55.225 --> 00:00:56.726
<i>It's sad how pathetic I am.</i>

22
00:00:56.727 --> 00:00:58.228
<i>But you know
who's even more pathetic?</i>

23
00:00:58.361 --> 00:01:00.397
<i>Someone who makes a show
about it.</i>

24
00:01:00.497 --> 00:01:02.733
<i>And anyone who listens to it.</i>

25
00:01:02.833 --> 00:01:05.535
<i>Lance Kingston is the one
who took those photos.</i>

26
00:01:05.536 --> 00:01:07.738
But he's not the guy
who sent it to you.

27
00:01:07.871 --> 00:01:09.506
Turns out your fan stole them.

28
00:01:09.606 --> 00:01:11.542
<i>Lance. he's just
a means to an end.</i>

29
00:01:11.675 --> 00:01:13.544
<i>He's a sacrificial pawn.</i>

30
00:01:35.999 --> 00:01:38.100
Perimeter breached.

31
00:01:38.101 --> 00:01:39.202
Ground floor.

32
00:01:39.302 --> 00:01:41.270
One casualty. Outer corridor.

33
00:01:41.271 --> 00:01:43.072
<i>Do you have visual?</i>

34
00:01:44.741 --> 00:01:46.142
Negative.

35
00:01:51.414 --> 00:01:53.884
You motherfuckers!

36
00:01:55.218 --> 00:01:57.353
Reload! Reload!

37
00:02:00.924 --> 00:02:02.325
On my lead.

38
00:02:02.425 --> 00:02:03.326
Moving.

39
00:02:03.426 --> 00:02:04.427
Agents under fire.

40
00:02:04.528 --> 00:02:05.662
We need backup immediately.

41
00:02:05.762 --> 00:02:06.797
<i>Copy.</i>

42
00:02:06.930 --> 00:02:08.732
<i>Backup's on the way.</i>

43
00:02:11.468 --> 00:02:13.904
No.

44
00:02:14.938 --> 00:02:16.406
Shut up.

45
00:02:16.507 --> 00:02:18.709
Shut... up.

46
00:02:18.809 --> 00:02:19.810
Please. don't.

47
00:02:22.779 --> 00:02:25.248
Hey. you take
one more fucking step...

48
00:02:25.348 --> 00:02:26.182
Hmm?

49
00:02:26.282 --> 00:02:27.984
Easy. now. We want to help.

50
00:02:28.118 --> 00:02:29.953
- I don't want to die.
- No one's gonna get hurt.

51
00:02:30.053 --> 00:02:32.122
Don't you fucking lie to her.

52
00:02:32.222 --> 00:02:33.289
Sir. just put the gun down.

53
00:02:33.389 --> 00:02:35.958
- Look. what's your name?
- Fuck you!

54
00:02:35.959 --> 00:02:39.530
That's my name.
Why you keeping them from me?

55
00:02:39.630 --> 00:02:41.297
- Keeping what from you. sir?
- My meds!

56
00:02:41.397 --> 00:02:44.267
- I need my goddamn meds.
- Okay.

57
00:02:44.367 --> 00:02:47.336
Okay. put the gun down.
let the woman go. and I...

58
00:02:47.337 --> 00:02:48.905
Hey!

59
00:02:49.773 --> 00:02:52.142
You think I don't
fucking see you over there?

60
00:02:52.242 --> 00:02:53.376
Huh?

61
00:02:54.678 --> 00:02:56.512
You want this little lady
to die?

62
00:02:56.513 --> 00:02:57.814
No! Sir. sir.

63
00:02:57.914 --> 00:03:00.684
- We do not.
- Then give me my goddamn meds!

64
00:03:00.784 --> 00:03:02.184
<i>Agent Lowell.</i>

65
00:03:02.185 --> 00:03:03.486
<i>is target acquired?</i>

66
00:03:03.587 --> 00:03:06.723
- Negative.
<i>- Reposition. Acquire target.</i>

67
00:03:08.291 --> 00:03:09.760
Miss.

68
00:03:09.860 --> 00:03:11.795
what's your name?

69
00:03:11.895 --> 00:03:13.496
- Melissa...
- Don't!

70
00:03:13.597 --> 00:03:16.432
Don't talk to her!

71
00:03:17.200 --> 00:03:19.302
- You talk to me!
- Command. target has been acquired.

72
00:03:19.402 --> 00:03:21.503
You understand?!

73
00:03:21.504 --> 00:03:23.506
Oh-ho-ho!

74
00:03:23.640 --> 00:03:24.941
I have the shot.

75
00:03:25.041 --> 00:03:26.943
This guy over here. huh?
This guy over here.

76
00:03:27.043 --> 00:03:28.812
he wants to kill me so bad
that he can taste it.

77
00:03:28.912 --> 00:03:30.581
Except. what if he misses. hmm?

78
00:03:30.681 --> 00:03:33.049
- And this little one takes the hit.
- Sir?

79
00:03:33.183 --> 00:03:34.718
Enough of this bullshit.

80
00:03:34.851 --> 00:03:36.519
Okay? Enough!

81
00:03:36.653 --> 00:03:38.221
Okay?

82
00:03:38.321 --> 00:03:41.024
I'm gonna count to three.
and either you get me

83
00:03:41.157 --> 00:03:44.360
- my goddamn meds or I'm gonna
blow her fucking head off. - Please. no. No.

84
00:03:44.460 --> 00:03:45.862
<i>Lowell. you're clear.</i>

85
00:03:45.962 --> 00:03:47.598
<i>Send it.</i>

86
00:03:48.699 --> 00:03:49.866
Okay?

87
00:03:49.966 --> 00:03:51.034
One.

88
00:03:51.167 --> 00:03:52.769
Just give him what he wants!

89
00:03:52.869 --> 00:03:54.904
- Two.
- Sir. you kill her.

90
00:03:54.905 --> 00:03:56.439
- we kill you!
<i>- Take the shot.</i>

91
00:03:56.539 --> 00:03:57.908
Three!

92
00:04:04.380 --> 00:04:06.883
What the fuck? What the fuck?

93
00:04:07.751 --> 00:04:09.219
I took the shot.

94
00:04:09.352 --> 00:04:11.387
Holy shit. What'd you do?

95
00:04:11.487 --> 00:04:13.356
Abort. abort!
Abort the exercise!

96
00:04:15.859 --> 00:04:18.128
That was a live fucking round.

97
00:04:18.228 --> 00:04:20.631
- Holy shit.
- Get O'Connor.

98
00:04:21.497 --> 00:04:22.532
O'Connor!

99
00:04:22.633 --> 00:04:24.635
We need medical. Stat!

100
00:04:25.936 --> 00:04:27.838
Secure your weapons now.

101
00:04:27.938 --> 00:04:30.173
- Magazine check.
- I got blanks.

102
00:04:31.708 --> 00:04:33.576
Same.

103
00:04:33.710 --> 00:04:34.978
Billy?

104
00:04:36.279 --> 00:04:37.848
Billy. we're unarmed.

105
00:04:37.948 --> 00:04:40.016
Okay? Put down the gun.

106
00:04:41.084 --> 00:04:42.819
Talk to us. Billy.

107
00:04:42.919 --> 00:04:45.121
Medical's coming.

108
00:04:48.591 --> 00:04:50.126
He's dead.

109
00:04:53.529 --> 00:04:54.898
I took the shot.

110
00:04:55.699 --> 00:04:57.367
<i>- Security.</i>
- Initiate lockdown.

111
00:04:57.467 --> 00:04:59.301
Now. We have an active shooter.

112
00:04:59.302 --> 00:05:01.805
This is not a drill.
I repeat. this is not a drill.

113
00:05:01.938 --> 00:05:04.107
<i>- Copy.</i>
- Billy. in about 30 seconds.

114
00:05:04.240 --> 00:05:05.441
the real deal is
barreling in here.

115
00:05:05.575 --> 00:05:07.043
and they will kill you.

116
00:05:07.143 --> 00:05:08.645
Hey. you don't want
any more blood on your hands.

117
00:05:08.779 --> 00:05:10.446
do you. Billy? Please.

118
00:05:10.546 --> 00:05:12.148
Hand me that weapon.

119
00:05:13.449 --> 00:05:16.219
Let me help you. Billy. okay?

120
00:05:17.387 --> 00:05:19.089
Hey.

121
00:05:26.096 --> 00:05:27.797
I don't fucking get it. man.

122
00:05:29.966 --> 00:05:32.535
Hey. what were you thinking?

123
00:05:33.469 --> 00:05:35.839
I had... I had the shot.

124
00:05:39.009 --> 00:05:40.476
I took the shot.

125
00:05:40.576 --> 00:05:42.578
<i>Attention. all personnel.</i>

126
00:05:42.679 --> 00:05:44.580
<i>This is an emergency.</i>

127
00:05:44.681 --> 00:05:46.349
<i>You are under lockdown.</i>

128
00:05:46.449 --> 00:05:48.985
<i>Remain in your location
until further notice.</i>

129
00:05:49.085 --> 00:05:50.653
<i>This is not a drill.</i>

130
00:05:50.754 --> 00:05:52.989
<i>I repeat. this is not a drill.</i>

131
00:06:01.164 --> 00:06:03.666
<i>"We cannot grow
when we are in shame.</i>

132
00:06:03.767 --> 00:06:08.037
<i>and we can't use shame
to change ourselves or others."</i>

133
00:06:08.038 --> 00:06:09.504
<i>Brené Brown.</i>

134
00:06:09.505 --> 00:06:12.475
So. Tom Milliken was shot?

135
00:06:12.575 --> 00:06:15.145
During a training exercise
for selectees

136
00:06:15.245 --> 00:06:16.846
from the Hostage Rescue Team.

137
00:06:16.847 --> 00:06:18.749
An exercise with live rounds?

138
00:06:18.849 --> 00:06:20.083
Well. there's
a lot to unpack here.

139
00:06:20.183 --> 00:06:21.851
which is why Rebecca
has asked the BAU

140
00:06:21.852 --> 00:06:22.953
to get eyes on it.

141
00:06:23.053 --> 00:06:24.220
God. does Alvez know yet?

142
00:06:24.354 --> 00:06:25.822
He's on scene with JJ.

143
00:06:27.357 --> 00:06:29.558
Tom Milliken
was like family to him.

144
00:06:29.559 --> 00:06:31.161
Oh.

145
00:06:31.261 --> 00:06:34.664
Brian. what have I told you
about phone calls on Saturdays?

146
00:06:34.765 --> 00:06:36.900
Emily. I wouldn't trouble you

147
00:06:37.033 --> 00:06:38.902
were it not of
the utmost importance.

148
00:06:39.035 --> 00:06:41.972
I have. in my possession.
evidence

149
00:06:42.072 --> 00:06:43.706
of a pre-crime.

150
00:06:43.807 --> 00:06:45.508
What the fuck is a "pre-crime"?

151
00:06:45.608 --> 00:06:47.543
- Is that Tara?
<i>- Hi. Brian.</i>

152
00:06:47.643 --> 00:06:48.912
<i>What's with this</i>

153
00:06:49.012 --> 00:06:50.613
pre-crime?

154
00:06:50.713 --> 00:06:52.682
<i>It's the thing that happens
before one commits said crime.</i>

155
00:06:52.783 --> 00:06:55.885
No. I get the term.
What is it you think you have?

156
00:06:55.886 --> 00:06:58.855
<i>Oh. dare I say. a manifesto.
of sorts.</i>

157
00:06:58.955 --> 00:07:00.923
Addressed to me by a fan.

158
00:07:00.924 --> 00:07:02.258
It says. and here I quote.

159
00:07:02.358 --> 00:07:05.728
"Some may call me a fan.
but He must call me God."

160
00:07:05.829 --> 00:07:08.765
<i>And since this same
declaration is typed</i>

161
00:07:08.865 --> 00:07:10.399
<i>over and over again like...</i>

162
00:07:10.400 --> 00:07:13.003
Do you remember Jack Nicholson's
character in <i>The Shining?</i>

163
00:07:13.103 --> 00:07:15.938
Like. he starts to go wacko
and he types this one sentence

164
00:07:15.939 --> 00:07:17.239
over and over and over.

165
00:07:17.240 --> 00:07:19.075
<i>"All work and no play makes..."</i>

166
00:07:19.175 --> 00:07:21.677
- Yeah. I've seen the movie.
<i>- Well. you should see this.</i>

167
00:07:21.778 --> 00:07:25.247
Not only has he repeatedly
typed his affirmation.

168
00:07:25.248 --> 00:07:27.717
but he's also printed it
into shapes.

169
00:07:27.818 --> 00:07:31.753
<i>The whole thing is so
wackadoodle. it's like...</i>

170
00:07:31.754 --> 00:07:33.957
and admittedly.
I'm no profiler...

171
00:07:34.057 --> 00:07:36.259
he's clearly itching
to do no good.

172
00:07:37.127 --> 00:07:38.461
Where are you?

173
00:07:38.561 --> 00:07:39.830
<i>Not far.</i>

174
00:07:39.930 --> 00:07:42.432
Literally around
the proverbial corner.

175
00:07:42.532 --> 00:07:44.100
You really should
take a look-see.

176
00:07:44.234 --> 00:07:46.601
<i>Okay. I'll have a visitor's
pass waiting for you.</i>

177
00:07:46.602 --> 00:07:48.270
God. when it rains. it pours.

178
00:07:48.271 --> 00:07:49.973
Okay. look. Dave and I
can handle this for you.

179
00:07:50.106 --> 00:07:51.441
Thank you.

180
00:07:51.541 --> 00:07:52.976
Yeah. I have to get
to the training facility.

181
00:07:53.109 --> 00:07:54.644
Yeah. yeah.

182
00:07:54.777 --> 00:07:57.113
<i>...or I'm gonna
blow her fucking head off.</i>

183
00:07:57.247 --> 00:07:59.515
<i>- One!
- Just give him</i>

184
00:07:59.615 --> 00:08:00.917
<i>- what he wants!
- Two!</i>

185
00:08:01.017 --> 00:08:02.986
<i>Sir. you kill her.
we kill you!</i>

186
00:08:03.119 --> 00:08:04.754
<i>- Three!</i>
- Who else knows?

187
00:08:04.855 --> 00:08:07.456
With the lockdown.
we're on a need-to-know basis.

188
00:08:07.457 --> 00:08:09.159
Director. A.G.. president.

189
00:08:09.292 --> 00:08:12.661
I'd say the news blackout holds
another 24 hours.

190
00:08:12.662 --> 00:08:13.830
But it's not like we have

191
00:08:13.964 --> 00:08:14.964
a lot of friends
in this administration.

192
00:08:14.965 --> 00:08:16.599
An agent-on-agent incident

193
00:08:16.699 --> 00:08:18.667
like this is exactly
the kind of pretext

194
00:08:18.668 --> 00:08:21.004
that they can use
to gut the department.

195
00:08:21.604 --> 00:08:23.106
Peter.

196
00:08:23.206 --> 00:08:25.474
I am so sorry.

197
00:08:25.475 --> 00:08:27.043
It's still hard to believe.

198
00:08:27.143 --> 00:08:28.478
Uh. Emily.
this is Peter O'Connor.

199
00:08:28.578 --> 00:08:29.812
Milliken's chief of staff.

200
00:08:29.946 --> 00:08:32.181
Tom spoke very highly of you
and your team.

201
00:08:32.182 --> 00:08:34.650
He brought you a case
recently. didn't he?

202
00:08:34.750 --> 00:08:37.486
He did. An equivocal
death investigation.

203
00:08:37.487 --> 00:08:40.190
And. incredibly.
he's now the subject of one.

204
00:08:40.323 --> 00:08:42.691
Well. not so equivocal.
I'm afraid.

205
00:08:42.692 --> 00:08:44.826
Agent Selectee Billy Lowell
fired the fatal shot.

206
00:08:44.827 --> 00:08:47.497
His weapon was the only one
with live rounds.

207
00:08:47.597 --> 00:08:50.133
Yes. that seems evident.
However. officially.

208
00:08:50.233 --> 00:08:52.001
there still needs to be
a determination

209
00:08:52.002 --> 00:08:53.835
of homicide or accidental death.

210
00:08:53.836 --> 00:08:55.071
Of course.

211
00:08:55.171 --> 00:08:57.307
I know it's been a while
since I was in training.

212
00:08:57.407 --> 00:08:59.342
but is it common now for H.R.T.

213
00:08:59.442 --> 00:09:02.044
to conduct an exercise
with actors and real weapons?

214
00:09:02.045 --> 00:09:04.714
Uh. no. it's not common.

215
00:09:04.814 --> 00:09:06.382
But Tom had his own methodology.

216
00:09:06.482 --> 00:09:07.984
And carte blanche from up top.

217
00:09:08.084 --> 00:09:10.453
If he wanted to do something.
he did it.

218
00:09:10.553 --> 00:09:12.788
In this case.
he felt that the selectees

219
00:09:12.889 --> 00:09:15.857
were in need of a far more
"real world" experience.

220
00:09:15.858 --> 00:09:19.996
So. did this exercise include
the entire selectee class?

221
00:09:20.096 --> 00:09:22.398
No. just Agents Helm.
Barlow and Lowell.

222
00:09:22.498 --> 00:09:23.833
They were a three-man unit.

223
00:09:23.934 --> 00:09:25.201
Well. Agent Lowell

224
00:09:25.335 --> 00:09:27.369
is already in custody.
but we are going to need

225
00:09:27.370 --> 00:09:29.672
to interview
Agents Helm and Barlow. as well.

226
00:09:29.772 --> 00:09:31.741
- Sure.
- Has the medical examiner

227
00:09:31.841 --> 00:09:33.409
taken possession of the body?

228
00:09:33.543 --> 00:09:35.544
Uh. he's doing that right now.

229
00:09:35.545 --> 00:09:37.413
Excuse me.

230
00:09:44.554 --> 00:09:46.056
Luke.

231
00:09:46.189 --> 00:09:48.091
I need a minute.

232
00:09:49.759 --> 00:09:53.229
I tried to tell him that maybe
he should sit this one out.

233
00:09:53.329 --> 00:09:55.065
Yeah.

234
00:10:00.937 --> 00:10:02.405
Brian.

235
00:10:02.538 --> 00:10:03.773
Tara.

236
00:10:03.906 --> 00:10:07.843
Well. I... what a delight it is
to see you again.

237
00:10:07.944 --> 00:10:10.112
- Uh. where's Emily?
- She thought it best

238
00:10:10.113 --> 00:10:13.616
that Tara and I took a look
at what you've got.

239
00:10:14.717 --> 00:10:16.752
Okay. Um...

240
00:10:16.886 --> 00:10:18.821
the thing is.
given our previous history.

241
00:10:18.921 --> 00:10:20.856
wouldn't it be better
if Tara and I were to...

242
00:10:20.957 --> 00:10:23.826
No. This way.

243
00:10:30.300 --> 00:10:32.368
"Some may call me a fan.

244
00:10:32.468 --> 00:10:35.638
but He must call me God."

245
00:10:35.738 --> 00:10:37.007
What'd I tell you?

246
00:10:37.107 --> 00:10:38.908
Redrum. Redrum.

247
00:10:39.009 --> 00:10:40.243
When did you get this?

248
00:10:40.343 --> 00:10:41.811
- Yesterday.
- Yesterday?

249
00:10:41.911 --> 00:10:43.513
I opened it today.

250
00:10:44.614 --> 00:10:46.782
Uh. oh.

251
00:10:46.882 --> 00:10:49.619
Postmark
Kensington. Pennsylvania.

252
00:10:50.420 --> 00:10:52.555
You guys have seen this
before. haven't you?

253
00:10:53.423 --> 00:10:55.158
Would you give us a second?

254
00:10:55.291 --> 00:10:57.293
