00:23:29.745 --> 00:23:32.147
And now he wants to be
called God

516
00:23:32.247 --> 00:23:35.150
because he feels he has
the power to show mercy.

517
00:23:35.250 --> 00:23:37.252
To choose
who lives and who dies.

518
00:23:37.352 --> 00:23:39.088
- Mm-hmm.
- But not before

519
00:23:39.188 --> 00:23:40.689
you pass him the torch.

520
00:23:40.790 --> 00:23:44.493
That's why he capitalizes
the "H" when he references you.

521
00:23:44.626 --> 00:23:47.897
Without your seal of approval.
he won't feel that. um.

522
00:23:47.997 --> 00:23:50.532
special something.

523
00:23:50.665 --> 00:23:54.502
That may be another reason
to send it to Garrity.

524
00:23:54.503 --> 00:23:56.305
Trying to get me
on the podcast again.

525
00:23:56.405 --> 00:23:59.674
Yeah. that's not gonna happen.

526
00:23:59.775 --> 00:24:02.044
Okay. but maybe if he heard

527
00:24:02.144 --> 00:24:04.678
someone else's voice
on the podcast.

528
00:24:04.679 --> 00:24:06.681
it would engage him enough
so that he gets

529
00:24:06.782 --> 00:24:09.017
careless enough
to reveal himself.

530
00:24:09.018 --> 00:24:10.585
Okay.

531
00:24:10.685 --> 00:24:13.022
- Who are you thinking?
- Me.

532
00:24:13.122 --> 00:24:14.723
Yes.

533
00:24:15.624 --> 00:24:17.126
No.

534
00:24:17.893 --> 00:24:20.762
If he's my fan. he's trying
to walk in my footsteps.

535
00:24:20.863 --> 00:24:23.165
which means he's read
every single one of your books.

536
00:24:23.265 --> 00:24:24.900
Hey. they're not how-to books.

537
00:24:25.034 --> 00:24:27.636
He respects you.

538
00:24:27.736 --> 00:24:29.471
You led the team
that led to my capture.

539
00:24:29.571 --> 00:24:32.741
If he hears your voice live
on Brian's podcast.

540
00:24:32.875 --> 00:24:34.844
I don't know
how he can not reach out.

541
00:24:34.944 --> 00:24:38.814
You are the only person
he might surrender to.

542
00:24:42.017 --> 00:24:43.485
I mean...

543
00:24:45.054 --> 00:24:46.922
...because he trusts you.

544
00:24:47.823 --> 00:24:49.057
You know I'm right.

545
00:24:49.058 --> 00:24:51.059
Otherwise. you wouldn't be here.

546
00:24:59.368 --> 00:25:00.469
Hey.

547
00:25:00.569 --> 00:25:02.137
- Sorry to interrupt.
- Not a problem.

548
00:25:03.172 --> 00:25:04.239
What do you need?

549
00:25:04.373 --> 00:25:06.508
In reviewing
the incident reports.

550
00:25:06.608 --> 00:25:08.677
we weren't able to find one
describing Milliken

551
00:25:08.777 --> 00:25:11.080
pulling his service weapon
on Agent Lowell.

552
00:25:11.213 --> 00:25:12.814
I wish I could say
I'm surprised.

553
00:25:12.915 --> 00:25:15.417
- Was a report filed?
- Not to me. but

554
00:25:15.517 --> 00:25:18.854
I am now hearing rumors
that many anonymous reports

555
00:25:18.954 --> 00:25:20.922
sent to the Office
of Professional Responsibility

556
00:25:20.923 --> 00:25:22.091
may have been slow-rolled.

557
00:25:22.191 --> 00:25:24.625
Friends in high places?

558
00:25:24.626 --> 00:25:26.761
It's all hearsay. right?

559
00:25:27.662 --> 00:25:29.164
All I know
from personal experience

560
00:25:29.264 --> 00:25:31.300
is he got results.

561
00:25:32.067 --> 00:25:33.968
If he passed you.
you were the best of the best.

562
00:25:33.969 --> 00:25:37.006
So. you're saying they were
willing to look the other way

563
00:25:37.106 --> 00:25:39.808
if he crossed the line
now and again?

564
00:25:39.942 --> 00:25:41.643
You're saying that.

565
00:25:41.743 --> 00:25:43.578
But I wouldn't disagree.

566
00:25:58.427 --> 00:26:00.562
It's this new class.

567
00:26:00.662 --> 00:26:01.796
Killing me.

568
00:26:01.897 --> 00:26:04.465
It's triggering
all my old habits.

569
00:26:04.466 --> 00:26:06.735
I'm just not...

570
00:26:06.835 --> 00:26:08.169
- I don't know.
- No.

571
00:26:08.170 --> 00:26:11.073
You don't get to end on.
"I don't know."

572
00:26:11.173 --> 00:26:12.507
Talk to me.

573
00:26:12.607 --> 00:26:14.076
It's Cindy.

574
00:26:14.176 --> 00:26:15.544
She's not happy.

575
00:26:16.478 --> 00:26:18.313
Come on. you guys...

576
00:26:18.413 --> 00:26:20.815
- you've been through worse.
- I know.

577
00:26:22.651 --> 00:26:25.154
That's the thing
with getting older and wiser.

578
00:26:25.287 --> 00:26:27.522
You start to realize
you don't have to spend

579
00:26:27.622 --> 00:26:29.491
the rest of your life
putting up with shit.

580
00:26:29.591 --> 00:26:31.860
Oh. so you-you think
you're putting up with...

581
00:26:31.994 --> 00:26:32.995
No. not me.

582
00:26:33.128 --> 00:26:34.195
Cindy.

583
00:26:34.196 --> 00:26:35.663
- Oh.
- Come on. she has spent

584
00:26:35.664 --> 00:26:38.533
the better part of her life
dealing with mine.

585
00:26:40.335 --> 00:26:42.003
You guys going to counseling?

586
00:26:42.004 --> 00:26:44.039
Yeah. twice a week.

587
00:26:45.507 --> 00:26:47.341
Still...

588
00:26:47.342 --> 00:26:49.043
it's me.

589
00:26:49.044 --> 00:26:51.646
I don't know
what the hell is going on.

590
00:26:51.746 --> 00:26:53.182
I'm bringing work home with me.

591
00:26:53.315 --> 00:26:55.484
I'm barking orders at her
like she's one of my trainees.

592
00:26:55.584 --> 00:26:57.219
It is bad. Luke.

593
00:26:59.054 --> 00:27:02.691
Look. a wise man once told me
that it's one thing

594
00:27:02.824 --> 00:27:05.627
to identify the problem.
and it's another thing

595
00:27:05.727 --> 00:27:06.861
to do the work.

596
00:27:06.962 --> 00:27:08.197
Words.

597
00:27:08.330 --> 00:27:11.266
Yeah. until you put them
into action.

598
00:27:12.801 --> 00:27:14.569
I just...

599
00:27:14.703 --> 00:27:17.871
don't know what I would do
without her.

600
00:27:17.872 --> 00:27:19.141
You know?

601
00:27:22.811 --> 00:27:25.981
Look. maybe you need
some time off.

602
00:27:30.552 --> 00:27:31.753
You're empty.

603
00:27:33.255 --> 00:27:35.824
- Want another?
- No.

604
00:27:36.825 --> 00:27:38.260
No. I'm good.

605
00:27:39.161 --> 00:27:40.529
Come on.

606
00:27:40.629 --> 00:27:42.931
One more round. On me.

607
00:27:45.700 --> 00:27:46.568
Sure.

608
00:27:46.668 --> 00:27:49.138
Attaboy. That's the spirit.

609
00:28:05.954 --> 00:28:07.256
Hey. so it looks like

610
00:28:07.356 --> 00:28:11.126
we have to reinterview
all the selectees.

611
00:28:13.595 --> 00:28:15.364
You okay?

612
00:28:18.267 --> 00:28:20.502
It's not fair.

613
00:28:21.703 --> 00:28:23.238
Death rarely is.

614
00:28:23.338 --> 00:28:25.140
Not death.

615
00:28:26.908 --> 00:28:28.377
Grief.

616
00:28:34.116 --> 00:28:35.684
I'm sorry.

617
00:28:37.018 --> 00:28:39.654
You're the last person
I should be saying that to.

618
00:28:39.754 --> 00:28:41.790
No. I... I get it.

619
00:28:41.890 --> 00:28:43.192
Ah. I...

620
00:28:44.025 --> 00:28:46.595
I don't want you to think
that I'm trying to compare

621
00:28:46.695 --> 00:28:49.831
what you went through
to what I'm going through.

622
00:28:49.964 --> 00:28:51.900
Luke. stop.

623
00:28:52.000 --> 00:28:54.236
I understand.

624
00:28:54.336 --> 00:28:57.206
Everyone experiences grief
in their own way.

625
00:28:58.273 --> 00:29:00.642
I mean. Jesus.
it's been over a year.

626
00:29:00.775 --> 00:29:06.014
and not a day goes by
where I don't see Will's eyes

627
00:29:06.115 --> 00:29:08.550
or his sense of humor
in the boys.

628
00:29:09.584 --> 00:29:12.854
It's. um...
it's. uh. fucking brutal.

629
00:29:14.489 --> 00:29:16.858
Grief is not kind.

630
00:29:16.991 --> 00:29:19.661
Or rational or-or fair.

631
00:29:21.062 --> 00:29:22.997
But trust me.

632
00:29:23.132 --> 00:29:27.469
if you don't give yourself
the space to feel.

633
00:29:27.569 --> 00:29:30.839
if you cut yourself off
from those feelings...

634
00:29:32.407 --> 00:29:33.975
...it gets way worse.

635
00:29:35.677 --> 00:29:37.279
Yeah.

636
00:29:38.213 --> 00:29:39.548
So?

637
00:29:40.515 --> 00:29:46.388
What can we do
to give you the space you need?

638
00:29:50.992 --> 00:29:53.162
I thought I could
take the lead on this case.

639
00:29:53.262 --> 00:29:55.430
but I. uh...

640
00:29:55.530 --> 00:29:57.699
I need you and Tyler to...

641
00:29:57.799 --> 00:29:59.534
have my back.

642
00:29:59.634 --> 00:30:01.102
We got you.

643
00:30:04.373 --> 00:30:05.706
We got you.

644
00:30:05.707 --> 00:30:07.408
Thanks.

645
00:30:19.221 --> 00:30:21.790
<i>Agent Barlow. apart from
his actions during training.</i>

646
00:30:21.890 --> 00:30:24.493
<i>what else can you tell us
about Milliken's behavior?</i>

647
00:30:25.760 --> 00:30:27.396
I didn't really spend
any time with him

648
00:30:27.496 --> 00:30:29.764
outside of the exercises.

649
00:30:29.864 --> 00:30:33.902
What about before briefings
or after training exercises?

650
00:30:34.002 --> 00:30:36.037
Maybe you checked in
during his office hours?

651
00:30:36.137 --> 00:30:38.640
Well. yeah. sometimes. I guess.

652
00:30:39.941 --> 00:30:41.443
I suppose it was true
that he was all

653
00:30:41.576 --> 00:30:43.312
fire and brimstone
during the training.

654
00:30:43.412 --> 00:30:46.114
but lately. when he was alone...

655
00:30:47.916 --> 00:30:49.818
...it started to get weird.

656
00:30:51.085 --> 00:30:52.454
How so?

657
00:30:54.055 --> 00:30:57.259
Well. I went to see him
about this procedural question.

658
00:30:59.294 --> 00:31:00.662
<i>And I walked in there.</i>

659
00:31:00.762 --> 00:31:02.597
<i>He was sitting behind his desk.</i>

660
00:31:02.697 --> 00:31:05.200
<i>And he didn't see me.
but I saw him.</i>

661
00:31:07.469 --> 00:31:10.138
<i>And he was... crying.</i>

662
00:31:13.608 --> 00:31:15.444
<i>Yeah. Joey told me about it.</i>

663
00:31:15.544 --> 00:31:17.979
He said he was.
like. ugly crying.

664
00:31:18.112 --> 00:31:19.548
It didn't make any sense.

665
00:31:19.648 --> 00:31:22.651
I mean. yeah. we were
prepping for our next eval.

666
00:31:22.751 --> 00:31:24.253
but it was a low-stress day.

667
00:31:24.353 --> 00:31:26.855
Clearly. something
got under his skin.

668
00:31:28.957 --> 00:31:30.292
Let me tell you something.

669
00:31:30.392 --> 00:31:32.727
I've known Tom Milliken
for over 20 years.

670
00:31:32.827 --> 00:31:34.028
- I've never...
- Look. Luke...

671
00:31:34.128 --> 00:31:35.496
...never once seen him cry.

672
00:31:35.497 --> 00:31:37.666
Yeah. well. neither have I. technically.

673
00:31:37.766 --> 00:31:39.800
Okay?
It's just what Joey told me.

674
00:31:39.801 --> 00:31:41.135
Joey also couldn't tell us

675
00:31:41.236 --> 00:31:43.003
what was troubling
Agent Milliken.

676
00:31:43.004 --> 00:31:44.539
Can you?

677
00:31:45.540 --> 00:31:47.342
Okay. not for sure.

678
00:31:47.442 --> 00:31:50.111
There was a rumor...

679
00:31:50.211 --> 00:31:51.846
his wife was leaving him.

680
00:31:52.881 --> 00:31:54.015
Cindy? Nah.

681
00:31:54.115 --> 00:31:56.651
- Is that his wife?
- Yeah.

682
00:31:56.751 --> 00:31:58.987
Look. like I said. I can't say

683
00:31:59.120 --> 00:32:01.322
100% for certain
that his wife was leaving him.

684
00:32:01.323 --> 00:32:04.025
it was just something
I overheard.

685
00:32:05.594 --> 00:32:07.362
Are you okay?

686
00:32:21.343 --> 00:32:22.844
Cindy.

687
00:32:22.944 --> 00:32:24.178
Luke.

688
00:32:24.279 --> 00:32:25.647
It's good to see you.

689
00:32:25.747 --> 00:32:28.417
- I'm so sorry.
- Mm.

690
00:32:33.655 --> 00:32:36.124
We took this the day
he retired from the Army.

691
00:32:36.224 --> 00:32:37.759
Yeah.

692
00:32:38.860 --> 00:32:41.496
Yeah. I remember those days.

693
00:32:41.596 --> 00:32:43.632
New deployment every six months.

694
00:32:43.732 --> 00:32:45.434
Long phone calls home.

695
00:32:45.534 --> 00:32:47.702
- Or no phone calls for weeks.
- Yeah.

696
00:32:47.802 --> 00:32:49.203
After he retired.

697
00:32:49.304 --> 00:32:50.705
he said we'd finally
settle down.

698
00:32:50.805 --> 00:32:53.642
Buy a house.
stop moving from base to base.

699
00:32:54.709 --> 00:32:57.745
You know. he told me that

700
00:32:57.746 --> 00:33:01.550
the best decision he ever made
was joining the FBI.

701
00:33:01.650 --> 00:33:03.551
Said it felt like
you two finally...

702
00:33:03.552 --> 00:33:06.054
Finally had time for each other.

703
00:33:06.187 --> 00:33:07.856
- Yeah.
- Right.

704
00:33:11.560 --> 00:33:13.328
Sometimes the people
that help others the most.

705
00:33:13.428 --> 00:33:16.931
they just can't seem
to help themselves.

706
00:33:18.166 --> 00:33:20.068
I'm not sure what you mean.

707
00:33:23.738 --> 00:33:25.239
Cindy. the BAU is in the process

708
00:33:25.340 --> 00:33:27.442
of putting the pieces together
of what happened.

709
00:33:27.542 --> 00:33:30.110
and some information
has come to light

710
00:33:30.111 --> 00:33:35.248
that suggest Tom might have been
acting out self-destructively.

711
00:33:35.249 --> 00:33:38.520
That. uh. maybe he was suicidal.

712
00:33:39.421 --> 00:33:41.055
Tom?

713
00:33:41.155 --> 00:33:42.456
Okay. who told you that?

714
00:33:42.457 --> 00:33:44.258
I'm not at liberty to say.

715
00:33:44.359 --> 00:33:46.428
Absolutely not. Luke.

716
00:33:46.528 --> 00:33:48.597
And I'm not just saying that
because I'm his wife.

717
00:33:48.697 --> 00:33:51.965
Cindy. were you leaving him?

718
00:33:51.966 --> 00:33:53.435
Wow.

719
00:33:53.535 --> 00:33:56.771
I-I wouldn't ask
if I didn't have to.

720
00:33:56.905 --> 00:33:58.272
I-I don't even believe it.

721
00:33:58.373 --> 00:34:01.510
It's just that one of
Tom's trainees saw him

722
00:34:01.610 --> 00:34:05.646
here in his office. alone.
crying hysterically.

723
00:34:05.647 --> 00:34:07.115
Oh.

724
00:34:07.215 --> 00:34:12.487
One man sees another man crying.
and so he must be suicidal?

725
00:34:13.888 --> 00:34:15.657
Luke. you're
a behavioral profiler.

726
00:34:15.790 --> 00:34:17.426
You should know better.

727
00:34:23.197 --> 00:34:28.302
I know Tom was struggling with
how much he was hurting you.

728
00:34:30.304 --> 00:34:31.805
Yes.

729
00:34:31.806 --> 00:34:33.408
Yes. 30-plus years

730
00:34:33.508 --> 00:34:37.412
of Tom burying his feelings
was killing our relationship.

731
00:34:37.512 --> 00:34:41.149
But Tom was nothing
if not "never say die." right?

732
00:34:43.184 --> 00:34:45.620
I mean. he found
a new therapist.

733
00:34:45.720 --> 00:34:47.522
he got on new medication.

734
00:34:47.656 --> 00:34:49.023
and finally
he was getting in touch

735
00:34:49.123 --> 00:34:50.824
with his emotions. his truth.

736
00:34:50.825 --> 00:34:52.761
And yes. recently.
it made him cry.

737
00:34:52.861 --> 00:34:54.295
which was good for him.

738
00:34:54.395 --> 00:34:56.197
And for us.

739
00:34:57.432 --> 00:34:59.400
So. you weren't
getting a divorce?

740
00:34:59.501 --> 00:35:01.169
As long as he was
doing the work.

741
00:35:01.269 --> 00:35:03.505
I was never gonna leave him.

742
00:35:05.173 --> 00:35:07.375
And I made sure he knew that.

743
00:35:11.680 --> 00:35:13.682
Well. so. then.
as far as you're concerned.

744
00:35:13.782 --> 00:35:18.386
the only thing Tom was
having trouble with was work?

745
00:35:19.353 --> 00:35:23.525
For men like Tom. who felt
a profound responsibility

746
00:35:23.625 --> 00:35:26.360
to prepare the next generation
of warriors.

747
00:35:26.461 --> 00:35:28.296
he had a hard time deciding

748
00:35:28.396 --> 00:35:31.533
whether he wanted
to be loved or feared.

749
00:35:34.903 --> 00:35:36.705
I loved him.

750
00:35:36.805 --> 00:35:39.974
I'm not sure
many others would agree.

751
00:35:40.809 --> 00:35:42.711
And with this last class.

752
00:35:42.811 --> 00:35:45.480
he told me that the best lesson
he could give them

753
00:35:45.580 --> 00:35:47.081
was to drop them.

754
00:35:47.916 --> 00:35:49.417
That's why
that young man decided

755
00:35:49.551 --> 00:35:51.786
to take Tom's life. isn't it?

756
00:35:54.222 --> 00:35:56.424
Isn't it?

757
00:36:02.931 --> 00:36:05.233
Hey. Y-You got a minute?

758
00:36:05.333 --> 00:36:06.601
Yeah. of course.

759
00:36:06.701 --> 00:36:08.236
All right. Look. I've been...

760
00:36:09.871 --> 00:36:12.907
...doing like we said
and following the evidence.

761
00:36:13.041 --> 00:36:14.275
where it takes me.

762
00:36:14.408 --> 00:36:18.580
And obviously Lowell shot Tom.
and. uh...

763
00:36:20.048 --> 00:36:23.685
...he neither accidentally
nor intentionally

764
00:36:23.785 --> 00:36:25.520
took his life.

765
00:36:25.620 --> 00:36:27.989
- So. suicide?
- No.

766
00:36:29.223 --> 00:36:31.392
And I don't know why
I didn't think about this

767
00:36:31.492 --> 00:36:33.294
from the start. but...

768
00:36:33.394 --> 00:36:35.930
although Tom was fixated
on Lowell's shortcomings.

769
00:36:36.030 --> 00:36:38.299
he would've held
his whole unit accountable.

770
00:36:38.432 --> 00:36:40.268
All for one. one for all.

771
00:36:40.368 --> 00:36:42.136
That kind of bond is everything.

772
00:36:42.236 --> 00:36:43.971
And if Tom
was threatening D.O.R..

773
00:36:43.972 --> 00:36:47.208
he was threatening to drop
all three agent selectees.

774
00:36:47.308 --> 00:36:49.343
including
Agents Barlow and Helm.

775
00:36:49.443 --> 00:36:52.480
So. you think
one or both of them...

776
00:36:52.581 --> 00:36:56.918
